					<h3>Winter humpbacks, dolphins and gray whales</h3>
					<p><img src="/images/234.jpg" alt="Winter Humpbacks while Whale Watching in Monterey Bay California with Stagnaro Charters"></p>
					<p>Saturday, December 20, 2014: Whale Watching on Velocity we saw 15 humpback whales! The whales were breaching, pec slapping, tail throws… Amazing activity!</p>
					<p>Sunday, December 21, 2014: We saw 6 humpback whales and around 200 common dolphins! Clear water allowed to see them under the boat as they rode alongside. Then at the end of the trip a small humpback breached by the boat countless times!</p>
					<img src="/images/235.jpg" alt="xxxxxxxxxxx while Whale Watching in Monterey Bay California with Stagnaro Charters">
					<p class="cr">Common Dolphins bow riding alongside Velocity. Monterey Bay, CA Photo: Michael Nelson</p>
					<p>Tuesday, December 23, 2014: A variety of species today! We saw 4 gray whales and 9 humpback whales. The sun was shining for us today on the 3rd day of winter!</p>
